name: Zixuan Song
headline: Software Engineer at Amazon
creator: False
bio:
Explorer, innovator, and first principles thinker. I am a Software Engineer with 3+ years of experience at Amazon. I have led teams of engineers and delivered robust and scalable solutions that power the day-to-day operations of airlines within our aviation vertical. I am a self-motivator, a fast learner, an effective communicator, and a team player. My motto is: Don’t just work smart, work smart and hard.  

During my professional career, I have always followed these two core tenets that have helped me succeed:
1. Unrelenting pursuit of truth: From learning a new software framework to tackling an elusive bug, one must dispel the notion of magic. Every system, no matter how large or complex, can be unraveled to its source. Only when we rigorously interrogate the truth do we gain concrete understandings and valuable insights.
2. Uncompromising integrity: Instead of taking shortcuts, I put forth my utmost effort in delivering solutions. When confronted with imperfections, I embrace criticism and strive to do better. I am continuously seeking opportunities for improvement. And when they are identified, I eagerly work with my team to integrate them into our product.

My passion for creating software extends beyond my current role. I have additional interests in reverse engineering, high performance computing, and embedded systems. I am always open to new opportunities in the role of a software engineer, where I can leverage my experience and values to drive impactful solutions.

headline: Software Development Engineer 2 at Amazon | Ex-PlayStation, Oracle
creator: False
bio:
I am currently working as a Software Development Engineer 2 at Amazon in the Amazon FinTech Org. I hold a Master's Degree in Software Engineering from San Jose State University (SJSU). While pursuing my Master's, I interned at PlayStation as a Software Engineer where I worked on automating & improving the release process of PlayStation's internal Telemetry packages.
 
Prior to this, I worked at Oracle as an Applications Developer 1 for the Document Management System (DMS) module of Oracle Banking Platform (OBP), a premium banking product catering to the world’s top-tier banks. I steered the module's frontend & backend development activities for incorporating multiple new features & was also the contingent Single Point of Contact (SPoC) of the module.

TECHNICAL SKILLS:

Programming Languages: Java, JavaScript, TypeScript 
Frameworks: Apache Kafka, Express, Oracle ADF, Spring MVC, Java Swing, J2EE
Web Development: React, Redux, NodeJS, REST API, Bootstrap, HTML, CSS, GraphQL, JWT, Handlebars templating language 
Databases: MySQL, MongoDB 
Others: Amazon AWS, Git, SVN, BitBucket, Eclipse, VSCode, Oracle JDeveloper, Oracle Weblogic, Android, Hibernate, NPM
